article.headline: Oral Roberts 72, Southern Utah 66
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Luke Spencer-Gardner's 3-pointer from the deep left corner with 1:16 remaining gave Oral Roberts its first lead since midway through the second half, and the Golden Eagles held on to beat Southern Utah 72-66 Monday. Caleb Green led Oral Roberts (16-5, 7-2 Mid-Continent) with 27 points and 12 rebounds. Mickey Michalec scored 15 points for the Eagles and Ken Tutt added 13. DeAngelo Newsom scored 15 points for Southern Utah (10-10, 3-6). Lubor Olsovsky scored 13 points, and Steve Barnes and Rand Janes had 12 and 11 points, respectively. Spencer-Gardner had gone 0-for-7 until he hit his 3-pointer with the shot clock winding down to give the Eagles a 67-66 lead. Before that, Oral Roberts' last lead was 46-43 with 13:27 to play. Tutt made two free throws with 14 seconds to play to give the Eagles a three-point lead. After Barnes missed a 3-pointer with 1.4 seconds left, Green clinched it with a free throw. His second foul shot missed, but Barnes inadvertently tipped it into the Oral Roberts basket at the buzzer.
